{"name":"Empty Soul","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p>At 6th level, you learn to fight without being weighed down by your own life energy. When you have no ki remaining, your movement speed increases by 10 feet and you gain temporary hit points equal to your Wisdom modifier (minimum of 1) at the start of each of your turns.</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"ATLAS","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"flat"},"requirements":"Monk 6 (Void (ATLAS))","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/mighty-force.svg","flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"subclassFeature","source":"ATLAS","hash":"empty%20soul_monk_phb_void%20(atlas)_atlas_6_atlas","propDroppable":"subclassFeature"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.","hash":"d539a3eeead5d1a2cbb5350ac4eeb41be10927b2"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1682004192532,"modifiedTime":1682004192532,"lastModifiedBy":"pjd4PUp7eb3ERd0h"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"pjd4PUp7eb3ERd0h":3},"_id":"0yfZU00redblr3yx"}
{"name":"Tranquility","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\"><p>Beginning at 11th level, you can enter a special meditation that surrounds you with an aura of peace. At the end of a long rest, you gain the effect of a @spell[sanctuary] spell that lasts until the start of your next long rest (the spell can end early as normal). The saving throw DC for the spell equals 8 + your Wisdom modifier + your proficiency bonus.</p><div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"PHB","activation":{"type":"special","cost":null,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":"","actionType":"save","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"wis","dc":null,"scaling":"wis"},"requirements":"Way of the Open Hand 11","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"effects":[],"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"subclassFeature","source":"PHB","hash":"tranquility_monk_phb_open%20hand_phb_11_phb","propDroppable":"subclassFeature"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.","hash":"fe591615b9cbb1a791bf27823a6f3212bf3b63a7"}},"img":"icons/magic/nature/tree-spirit-blue.webp","_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1682004192946,"modifiedTime":1682004192946,"lastModifiedBy":"pjd4PUp7eb3ERd0h"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"pjd4PUp7eb3ERd0h":3},"_id":"1nLmZ7u7rMXCaScM"}
{"name":"Touch of Death","type":"feat","system":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><p>Starting when you choose this tradition at 3rd level, your study of death allows you to extract vitality from another creature as it nears its demise. When you reduce a creature within 5 feet of you to 0 hit points, you gain temporary hit points equal to your Wisdom modifier + your monk level (minimum of 1 temporary hit point).</p></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"SCAG","activation":{"type":"","cost":0,"condition":""},"duration":{"value":null,"units":""},"target":{"value":null,"width":null,"units":"","type":""},"range":{"value":null,"long":null,"units":""},"uses":{"value":null,"max":"","per":null,"recovery":""},"consume":{"type":"","target":null,"amount":null},"ability":null,"actionType":"other","attackBonus":0,"chatFlavor":"","critical":{"threshold":null,"damage":""},"damage":{"parts":[],"versatile":""},"formula":"","save":{"ability":"","dc":null,"scaling":"flat"},"requirements":"Monk 3 (Long Death)","recharge":{"value":null,"charged":false}},"img":"modules/plutonium/media/icon/mighty-force.svg","flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"subclassFeature","source":"SCAG","hash":"touch%20of%20death_monk_phb_long%20death_scag_3_scag","propDroppable":"subclassFeature"},"scene-packer":{"sourceId":"Item.","hash":"86e0f7e87de7fe12fc3f49cbf3e70b2a1652c0ce"}},"effects":[],"_stats":{"systemId":"dnd5e","systemVersion":"2.0.3","coreVersion":"10.288","createdTime":1682004193134,"modifiedTime":1682004193134,"lastModifiedBy":"pjd4PUp7eb3ERd0h"},"folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"pjd4PUp7eb3ERd0h":3},"_id":"2a0u0PjAi2La2ufl"}
{"name":"Way of the Sun Soul","type":"subclass","system":{"description":{"value":"<div class=\"mb-2 ve-flex-col\"><p><i class=\"ve-muted\">Note: importing a class as an item is provided for display purposes only. If you wish to import a class to a character sheet, please use the importer on the sheet instead.</i></p><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--0\"><div data-source=\"XGE\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><h2 class=\"rd__h rd__h--1\" data-title-index=\"951\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Way of the Sun Soul</span><span class=\"ve-flex-vh-center\"> <span class=\"rd__title-link \"><span class=\"help-subtle\" title=\"Xanathar’s Guide to Everything\">XGE</span> p35</span><span class=\"rd__h-toggle ml-2 clickable\" data-rd-h-toggle-button=\"true\">[–]</span></span></h2> <p>Monks of the Way of the Sun Soul learn to channel their life energy into searing bolts of light. They teach that meditation can unlock the ability to unleash the indomitable light shed by the soul of every living creature.</p><div data-source=\"XGE\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"952\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Radiant Sun Bolt</span><span class=\"ve-flex-vh-center\"> <span class=\"rd__title-link \"><span class=\"help-subtle\" title=\"Xanathar’s Guide to Everything\">XGE</span> p35</span><span class=\"rd__h-toggle ml-2 clickable\" data-rd-h-toggle-button=\"true\">[–]</span></span></h3> <p>Starting when you choose this tradition at 3rd level, you can hurl searing bolts of magical radiance.</p><p>You gain a new attack option that you can use with the @action[Attack] action. The special attack is a ranged spell attack with a range of 30 feet. You are proficient with it, and you add your Dexterity modifier to its attack and damage rolls. Its damage is radiant, and its damage die is a [[/r d4]]. This die changes as you gain monk levels, as shown in the Martial Arts column of the Monk table.</p><p>When you take the @action[Attack] action on your turn and use this special attack as part of it, you can spend 1 ki point to make the special attack twice as a bonus action. When you gain the Extra Attack feature, this special attack can be used for any of the attacks you make as part of the @action[Attack] action.</p></div></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><div data-source=\"XGE\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"953\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Searing Arc Strike</span><span class=\"ve-flex-vh-center\"> <span class=\"rd__title-link \"><span class=\"help-subtle\" title=\"Xanathar’s Guide to Everything\">XGE</span> p35</span><span class=\"rd__h-toggle ml-2 clickable\" data-rd-h-toggle-button=\"true\">[–]</span></span></h3> <p>At 6th level, you gain the ability to channel your ki into searing waves of energy. Immediately after you take the @action[Attack] action on your turn, you can spend 2 ki points to cast the @spell[burning hands] spell as a bonus action.</p><p>You can spend additional ki points to cast @spell[burning hands] as a higher-level spell. Each additional ki point you spend increases the spell's level by 1. The maximum number of ki points (2 plus any additional points) that you can spend on the spell equals half your monk level.</p></div></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><div data-source=\"XGE\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"954\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Searing Sunburst</span><span class=\"ve-flex-vh-center\"> <span class=\"rd__title-link \"><span class=\"help-subtle\" title=\"Xanathar’s Guide to Everything\">XGE</span> p35</span><span class=\"rd__h-toggle ml-2 clickable\" data-rd-h-toggle-button=\"true\">[–]</span></span></h3> <p>At 11th level, you gain the ability to create an orb of light that erupts into a devastating explosion. As an action, you magically create an orb and hurl it at a point you choose within 150 feet, where it erupts into a sphere of radiant light for a brief but deadly instant.</p><p>Each creature in that 20-foot-radius sphere must succeed on a Constitution saving throw or take [[/r 2d6]] radiant damage. A creature doesn't need to make the save if the creature is behind total cover that is opaque.</p><p>You can increase the sphere's damage by spending ki points. Each point you spend, to a maximum of 3, increases the damage by [[/r 2d6]].</p></div></div><div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--1\"><div data-source=\"XGE\" class=\"rd__b  rd__b--2\"><h3 class=\"rd__h rd__h--2\" data-title-index=\"955\"> <span class=\"entry-title-inner\">Sun Shield</span><span class=\"ve-flex-vh-center\"> <span class=\"rd__title-link \"><span class=\"help-subtle\" title=\"Xanathar’s Guide to Everything\">XGE</span> p35</span><span class=\"rd__h-toggle ml-2 clickable\" data-rd-h-toggle-button=\"true\">[–]</span></span></h3> <p>At 17th level, you become wreathed in a luminous, magical aura. You shed bright light in a 30-foot radius and dim light for an additional 30 feet. You can extinguish or restore the light as a bonus action.</p><p>If a creature hits you with a melee attack while this light shines, you can use your reaction to deal radiant damage to the creature. The radiant damage equals 5 + your Wisdom modifier.</p></div></div></div></div>","chat":"","unidentified":""},"source":"XGE","identifier":"way-of-the-sun-soul","classIdentifier":"monk","advancement":[],"spellcasting":{"progression":"none","ability":""}},"flags":{"plutonium":{"page":"classes.html","source":"PHB","hash":"monk_phb","sourceSubclass":"XGE","hashSubclass":"monk_phb,state:sub-sun-soul-xge=b1","propDroppable":"subclass","filterValues":{"Source":{"TCE":1,"ERLW":1,"UA2020SubclassesPt3":0,"UAArtificerRevisited":1,"UAClassFeatureVariants":0,"UAArtificer":0,"PHB":1,"XGE":1,"UABarbarianPrimalPaths":0,"UARevisedSubclasses":0,"SCAG":1,"UA2020SubclassesPt1":0,"UABarbarianAndMonk":0,"UA2020SubclassesPt2":0,"UABardAndPaladin":0,"UABardBardColleges":0,"UAKitsOfOld":0,"VRGR":1,"UA2020SubclassesPt4":0,"UATheRangerRevised"